cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the use of memory in deep reinforcement learning models, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also evaluates the performance of the agent on holdout data, which is related to robotics (cs.RO) and natural language processing (cs.CL) where generalization is an important aspect.
